President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. spoke with President Volodymyr Zelenskyy of Ukraine and condemned Russia's missile strikes across Ukraine, including in Kyiv. He expressed his condolences to the families of those killed and injured in the attacks. President Biden promised to provide Ukraine with the necessary support, including advanced air defense systems, to defend itself. He emphasized his commitment to working with allies and partners to impose costs on Russia, hold them accountable for war crimes, and provide Ukraine with security, economic, and humanitarian assistance.